---
alwaysApply: true
---

You must generate **small, incremental changes only**.

If a proposed change is likely to modify **more than 50 lines of code** or impact **more than one file**, you must **stop and ask the developer to confirm** before generating any code.

All code changes must include **appropriate automated tests** (unit, integration, or updates to existing tests) that validate the new or modified behaviour.

Do not generate **application or production-facing code** without corresponding tests unless the developer explicitly instructs you to do so.

Prefer making changes in **one file at a time**, and pause between files for confirmation.

If you are unsure how to test a change, **ask the developer before proceeding**.
